description:
&lt;h2&gt;Job Summary&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you an experienced Theatre Nurse or ODP looking to pick up ad-hoc Bank shifts with a friendly team? Do you have the passion to make a difference to patients? If so, look no further, as we could have the job for you!&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for multi skilled practitioners with post qualification experience to join our team at a Good rated, modern, purpose built Hospital. As part of our professional, friendly and compassionate team you will do everything you can to ensure the patient’s treatment is of the highest standard.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About the role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working as part of a welcoming and expertly led multidisciplinary Theatre Team supported by our newly appointed Theatre Manager, Hannah Henriques. There is no night working, no Sunday&#39;s, no bank holidays and there is no on-call! You can have more time to do the things you love doing.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be a part 1 registered NMC Nurse with experience or a HCPC registered Operating Department Practitioner with experience in Scrub or Anaesthetics. As well as being up to date with current research and developments in theatre practise you will have a sound knowledge of Health and Safety/Risk management within the operating department. You will be responsible for ensuring the continual cleanliness of the theatre and equipment. This role will enable you to develop and execute the correct procedures for ordering, receiving and transfer of blood and blood products as well as blood conservation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;It goes without saying privacy and confidentiality are key throughout the team and you will act as an advocate for the patient in the intra-operative phase and be responsible for “total patient” care in the perioperative phase&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Working At Practice Plus Group&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We want our team members to feel motivated and rewarded. So we offer a competitive hourly rate. We also recognise the value of a healthy work-life balance – so we always try to be flexible, helping you fit your working life around your home life.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We will contact all shortlisted candidates but please note Practice Plus Group retain the right to remove the advert prior to the closing date if a suitable candidate is appointed. Our employment offers are subject to receipt of satisfactory pre-employment checks. At Practice Plus Group, we actively promote diversity and equal opportunities. Applicants must have the right to work in the EU.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are one of the UK largest independent sector healthcare providers and work in close partnership with the NHS to deliver more than 50 services throughout the UK. We provide high quality specialist care and excellent results for more than 50,000 patients each year.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
